
    xclip blog-post.html

Then hit the middle mouse button to paste

    aspell check blog-post.html

If you make any changes, it saves the old one as `blog-post.html.bak`.

    aspell check -H blog-post.html

From `man aspell`

    --mode=<string>, -e, -H, -t, -n
           Sets  the  filter  mode.  Mode is one of none, url, email, html,
           tex or nroff.  The alternative shortcut  options  are  '-e'  for
           email, '-H' for Html/Sgml, '-t' for Tex or '-n' for Nroff.


